1
00:00:01,300 --> 00:00:08,900
You arrive with a real event, not a blank dashboard.

2
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:16,000
The first job is not a pitch. It is knowing what matters in this room.

3
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:24,500
Scroll through the event read, then tap a question or ask your own.

4
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,300
Research stays private. You decide what eventually gets shared.

5
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:38,100
Pick the two links that make sense for this event. Not every link belongs in every room.

6
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:47,200
The preview makes the privacy boundary obvious before anyone scans.

7
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:55,000
Share the pass instead of hunting for the right app, profile, or contact method.

8
00:00:55,500 --> 00:01:02,500
The QR is designed for a real phone screen and a real conversation.

9
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:10,500
Capture the promise while it is fresh. Keep the context attached to the person.

10
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:19,100
The AI draft is editable. Copy it to the channel you already use, then mark it sent.

11
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:22,900
The goal is not more contacts. It is one real next step.
